TITLE: How Kyrsten Sinema's decision makes Democrats' 2024 Senate map tighter
SUMMARY: Arizona Sen. Kyrsten Sinema decided to shake up the political world on Friday by becoming an independent. The former Democrat is still caucusing with the party in the Senate, so the Democratic caucus still has 51 members. Now, instead of 49 Democrats and two independents within their ranks, the caucus has 48 Democrats and three independents.

SUMMARY: After several weeks of tense negotiations, President Joe Biden and House Republicans have reached an agreement in principle to raise the debt ceiling and cap spending.

TITLE: White House and House Republicans strike agreement in principle to raise debt ceiling
SUMMARY: White House and House GOP negotiators are racing to finalize a deal to raise the nation's debt limit as early as Saturday with time running perilously short and the risk of a first-ever US default growing.
CNN's David Gergen and Manu Raju say that the pressure is on House Speaker Kevin McCarthy to deliver a divided Republican conference to support an agreement on the debt ceiling.

Rep. Maxwell Frost (D-FL), the first member of Generation Z to serve in Congress, says Republicans are holding Americans hostage as they seek to cut spending in exchange for raising the nation's debt limit.

TITLE: Texas House of Representatives votes to impeach Attorney General Ken Paxton
SUMMARY: The Texas House of Representatives has voted to impeach Attorney General Ken Paxton, an unprecedented move following a legislative probe that faulted the third-term Republican for a yearslong pattern of corruption, including abusing his office's powers, retaliating against whistleblowers and obstructing justice.
The Texas House of Representatives has voted to impeach the state's Attorney General Ken Paxton. CNN correspondent Rosa Flores has more on the unprecedented move.
Rep. Tim Burchett (R-TN) explains to CNN's Jim Acosta why he's a "no" on any deal forged between White House and GOP negotiators to raise the nation's debt ceiling.

Texas Attorney General Ken Paxton is facing calls of impeachment from his own party. The GOP controlled House plans to vote tomorrow on the 20 impeachment articles against Paxton, who faces accusations of abusing his office. CNN's Ed Lavendera reports.

TITLE: Iowa governor signs bill to loosen child labor laws
SUMMARY: Iowa Republican Gov. Kim Reynolds signed a bill Friday that loosens child labor laws by extending the hours that teens can work and the establishments where they can be employed.

TITLE: New Iowa law restricts gender identity education, bans books with sexual content
SUMMARY: Iowa Gov. Kim Reynolds signed a sweeping bill into law Friday that will restrict education about gender identity and sexual orientation and ban books with certain sexual content from school libraries, as well as require schools to notify parents if their child asks to use a new name or pronoun.

TITLE: Harris becomes first woman to deliver commencement address at West Point
SUMMARY: Vice President Kamala Harris on Saturday became the first woman to deliver a commencement address at the  graduation ceremony at the US Military Academy in West Point, New York, warning graduates they were "an increasingly unsettled world where long standing principles are at risk."
